So ends Virgil's story. Aeneas after the war married Lavi- nia, and from them was sprung the line of kings who reigned in Alba Longa, as well as Romulus the founder of Rome. From his son Ascanius or Iulus, by Creusa, was said to be descended the Julian family, who⁷ in the person of the Caesars, became the imperial rulers of Rome in Virgil's days.
